   <question id="q1">
 
      <body>
         <p>Use the General Multiplication Rule to find the probability of the event that the engine is not overheating and a warning light shows up.</p>
      </body>
      <short_answer id="A"/>
      <part>
         <response input="A" match="*" score="1"/>
         <explanation>
            <p>We need to find
                  <?oxy_comment_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101111T153139-0500" comment="change correct?"?>P(<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101111T152856-0500"?>not
                  <?oxy_insert_end?>H and
                  <?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101111T152859-0500" content="not "?>W)<?oxy_comment_end?>.
                  Using the General Multiplication Rule:</p>
            <p>P(not H and W) = P(not H) * P(W | not H)</p>
            <p>Since P(H) = .03, P(not H) = .97, therefore P(not H and W) = .97 * .01 = .0097.</p>
         </explanation>
